  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The objective of this work was to investigate the effect of Ligilactobacillus salivarius&#xD;
      MP101 on the functional (Barthel index), cognitive (GDS/FAST) and nutritional (MNA) status,&#xD;
      and on the nasal and fecal inflammatory profiles of elderly living in a nursing home highly&#xD;
      affected by COVID-19.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
